This species has a wide range in distribution covering the entire Holarctic region, mainly Europe and North Africa (
Schuelke and Smetana 2015
). The records in the Nearctic region are regarded as those species introduced from Europe ( Klimaszewski et al. 2002 ). In Russia, the easternmost record reported is from West Siberia (
Schuelke and Smetana 2015
). We provide new distributional records of Aleochara morion as follows: new country record, Japan ( Hokkaido , Honshu ); new regional record, the Russian Far East.
